    <h1 class="opener__hed  -is-over-bg opener__hed--light" >        The Rising Cost of the Oil Industry’s Slow Death
    </h1>

        <h2 class="opener__dek  -is-over-bg opener__dek--light" >        Unplugged oil and gas wells accelerate climate change, threaten public health and risk hitting taxpayers’ pocketbooks. ProPublica and Capital &amp; Main found that the money set aside to fix the problem falls woefully short of the impending cost.
    </h2>
    
            <div class="article-meta-1  -is-over-bg article-meta-1--light">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mark-olalde">Mark Olalde</a>, ProPublica, and <span class="name">Nick Bowlin</span>, <a href="https://capitalandmain.com/">Capital &amp; Main</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-02-22EST05:00">Feb. 22, 5 a.m. EST</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

    
</div>
        
